values:
Its 2007 already, bloody hell!

Ive been quite busy. Was in two minds as to come back to uni or not at the beginning of the year. Alas though I am here. I'm about 82.39% sure that I am going to take a transfer onto a course at Bournemouth Arts Institute in Arts and Events Management. The thing is that I don't wanna change and think thats shit too and drop out. That'd be shite :( But ohwell, I'm sure I'll decide on it soon.

Started the year off at Ele's house. It was such a good night, pretty random. Me and Christine slept on the floor in the end! The day after new years eve was Rob, Ollie, Tom and Dunc's leaving party it was really good. Ive spoken to them all since theyve been gone and theyre having a good time which is ace. On the Thursday we went to Hogshead for Seb's 20th birthday, Eve gave me a present. It was some checkered braces, I still cant believe it, whata legened! The following week was the week that we all went back to uni, it invlbed alot of hong kong express chinese food.

Being back at Uni has been fine. It sucked going back to lessons but ohwell. Speant alot of time with my friend Jess which has been cool. We went to an indie rave a couple of weekends ago and last wednesday went to see Bloc Party which was immense. I also bought tickets for we are scientists as theyre playing at my SU nightclub aswell, its gunna be cool.

Started mentoring last week which was fun, but hard work. I had my second session this mornign  which was cool. My dad also came down this weekend, it was awesome but shite when he left. Kateys coming to stay this weekend though so thats something to look forward to and my train tickets just arrived for manchester! :) wooop! 

Im off to look at some houses ina minute, more stress! argh!

Week ahead: 176, hosue hunting, ele's bday plans, hotel bookings, katey, charity shopping, BRAND NEW (Y)

Ciao for now xx

I'm Home :)

Yaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaay.

Feels pretty darn good, can you tell? Have had a busy busy week. Last Friday I went to Southampton and stayed at Hannahs. It was Luke's 21st birthday so me Katey and Konstant went to Southampton. We all got ready at Hannahs before getting the taxi to Lukes.... drinking lots of Vodka and then going to a fab 80's club called REFLEX. I loved it. Was a really supurb night, I met some cool people too :) On Satruday me and Hannah had a lie-in then went to Pizza Hut with Boyis, Rory and Luke. Was great fun.

I did bugger all on Saturday and went out on Sunday, but iot wasnt great so I came home again. Monday morning started off with a finance test. It went reallllllly badly, I dont think Ive passed it at all, no joke :(. Oh well. I missed my lecture on Monday afternoon cause I really couoldnt be bothered.
Tuesday was my first day of mentor training. The course on whole was absolutely amazing. I really enjoyed it. I met a couple of people which was a real eye opened, will talk about it in the future I hope. Ive been placed at a school for girls as of January, I will see 4 girls a week for mentoring sessions, I really can't wait :)

Yesterday was a bit special. I went into uni for seminars and did soem work finishing up my 4000 word consultancy report!! Then came home and started cooking our christmas dinner. There was 7 of us in the end. We had a full roast dinner, pudding, mince pies, crackers and xmas toons. It was nice. After we ate we played some heated card games lol, Jess thouroughly proved that Im not the only person that gets far into them. Had a really good evening.

Got up with 10minutes to get ready for my two lectures this morning. Only 4 people showed up to my second one. Good turn out. I came home packed and said goodbye to my house chums and then got the bus-train-bus-ferry-bus home. I had 4 bags :( (bag lady).

 

Cant believe i've been at uni for a whole term now. Its so weird. Its been a real experience. not sure whether its been good or bad. But hey. Im home now, can't WAIT to see everyone again!!

 

Got Bloc Party tickets, secret gig at my uni nightclub, oh yeahhhhh :)

Its yet another late Friday night and Ive speant my evenign doing nothing.

This wee has been quite strange.

On Saturday my friend Fran came round and we had pizza hut before she drove us to Eesh's for a house party. Eesh lives with 27 people... it was and okay night! Had a few drink then came home and spoke to Eve on the net for agesss! 

I did absolutely nothing on sunday.... as per.

On monday i got my first finance assignment, it's pretty hard, I struggle with that lesson quite abit, eeek. I also got my grades back for my first assignment which was a poster presntation, i got a 2:1 :) Whoop!

On Tuesday after a hetic day at uni I came home and tidied before our friend Jess came round, myself, her and my two housemates Kat and Tom got really really fucked on vodka, beer and lemoncino. Eww. Played loads of drinking games ate garlic bread and crisp sandwhiches and went to bed pretty early since we'ed be drinking since 6!!

I was hanging all day Wednesday, felt pretty roug. Jess left at 12 and I speant most of the day milling around. In the evening I went to see Tenacious D and the pick of destiny! It was pretty good, shit for all those non Jack Black fans I can assume but I like it, naturally :) Spoke to Eve on the phone that night.

Yesterday I went to uni... (again) then speant most of the evening in front of the tv/ on the internet playing tetris. Sent out an e-mail to people about going out for christmas dinner which will, i hope, be awesome!! Medina quay again methinks!

Today after uni me Kat, Emma and Laura went to Poole to go to the new primark! Ive done 85.6% of my christmas shopping... I'm fucking skint now though :( Im gunna have to get some money out of my savings to tie me over for the xmas break! The weather today was shit, made my hair go whack and I looked like Doc.Brown from back to the future. (gay). Ive had a pretty boring evening. Been lounging about freezing my arse off (my heating is broke) and watching blunder which is my new tv love :D


Weekend: meeting chantell and cremer at the train station, work at frans house, christmas lights, pub, tv.... SUNDAY (school of rock!!)

Week ahead: Meeting Ed (?), Trip to the B.I.C, Focus group, Comedy Night, Staying at Hannahs in Southampton, Meeting Katey, Reflex!

Apologies to anyone reading this... it's quite possibly the most boring thing ive ever written :(

Really quick update,.

After all my worrying Battle of the bands on the whole was actually a hugely successful event and is set to be on local tv and in the newspaper! The finale is a week and 2days away and I've got so much that I need to organise by then.... eeek!

Ive been majorly upa dn down the past two days, Someone that I used to know died in a car crash on Monday, he was my age. I also then found out that the missing cymbal that dissapeard from the drumkit we used was stolen by someone I used to consider a freind, they did return it but I am not going to talk to them about it, or anything for that matter.

On friday im going to watch Eve and Jess' drama piece :) and then on Saturday it is Ele's 18th Birthday party, I am going a slighter more 'rounder edged' version of Brody Dalle of the Distillers :) Tomorrow I have lessons all day and have to hand in my psychology. Ryan was supposed to come adn get his cymbal today but never came, boys.

Hope everyone is a-okay,

Chloe xxx

Hey Guys!

I really do not have anything to talk about other than Battle of the Bands, How sad?!

 As some of you may know I (along with loads of good friends) have been organising this competition for the past couple of months. The winners will eventually get to play at this year's Isle Of Wight music festival which is  a wicked achievement.

The auditions are tomorrow and I am completely shitting my pants. All the negative thoughts havent gone yet and are starting to run me down, Im the most tired Ive been in such a long time. I hope that everything goes as planned tomorrow or I will feel so let down by myself. 

I just kinda had a bit of a dig at one of the band members over myspace for both fucking me around, wasting my time and being patronising and cocky. I feel awful about it now and wish I hadnt of written the message . I hope he takes it in the right way, he doesnt even know so he probably doesnt thin much of me.




Oh God.

Today has been alright,

Im thinking pretty negatively about school work and Battle of the Bands at the moment. Auditions for BOTB are this Thursday and any cock-up with reflect badly upon the oraganisation, namely me. I know that somethings going to go wrong. We hardly have any judges.


Oh man.


I think thats all for today - very short post. Hope everyone is well X

I HATE THIS NEW RICH TEXT, IT SUCKS :( 

I fancy updating but cant be bothered to bore you all with it long-windedly so will list it as I dont like the bullet point thing on here:

Katey got me and her RHCP tickets today, OMG I can't wait, it's the day after my birthday which will be a fantastic way of celebrating.

Katey stayed on Weds, we watched too much TV and ate curry.

Eve is on holiday and I miss her :(

Been in hospital this week for allergy testing but they thin now that it is a skin disorder because everything came up negative.

Have got an open day at Winchester Uni tomorrow.

Battle of the Bands auditions are on Thursday and Friday - Holy Shit

Not much else to say, I've done nothing in my Half-term week except Battle of the Bands stuff, e.g myspace promo. Ive not done any school work, dammit :X. 

I really do hate this box thing, ergh! I'm listening to the Artic Monkeys album on myspace so I can at least say Ive heard theyre album before I make my mind up on them.

Well, well, well

Have had yet another busy week. I didn't go out with Emma in the end last Friday. On Saturday I met Eve on the bus and we made our way to Chichester. The journey was rather amusing thans to some drunken blokes on the train, i started playing Sudoku, and now I'm hooked..... oh dear. We got to Seb's and did a bit of shopping before going to his place and watching family guy, twas cool. I felt really uncomfetable until everyone arrived and the alcohol started flowing. most of Seb's mates are really cool :)

On Sunday morning I woke up at 7:00am and couldn't get back to sleep. Kayleigh Seb's flatmate made me breakfast and I watched Hollyoaks. Eve and Seb got up and we chilled before they walked me back to the train. i didnt pay to get home which was great, and then my General Studies teacher was sat at the ferry terminal so I had someone to sit and talk to on the boat back to the Island.

On Sunday evening I walked to work and met Christine, she came back to mine and we had some dinner, didnt do any work though which was a bit gay, but it's fine. On Monday Eve very kindly took myslef and Chris to Sandown so we could talk in one of their Sixth Form assembeleys about Battle Of the Bands, Emily was there and so she put up the posters for me :)

On Tuesday I felt abit crappy and went into school anyways, just for our lesson to be cancelled, now theres a surprise. On Wednesday morning I speant most of my time in TuckShop with Rob doing a stock take for the accountant lady because spparantly we are in really bad debt, pish. That afternoon Laura came round and we watched some quality tele before going to Katey's house for some supremely cooked Haggis, yummers.

On Thursday morning I went to Ryde high-school with Amy and Jess and our new Arts faculty manager Mr.Lines to talk to the year 11's about Battle Of the bands, there was quite alot of interest.

On Friday I had another one of the pointless days at school. At lunch Laura drove me and Christine into town where we met Eve and bought our Euro-millions tickets, didn't win though :( After that we went to Mr.T's for lunch before I was dropped at home. That evening Laura and Katey came round for tea. Katey went home and Jess arrived and we went to the cinema and met Shaz where we watched 'Memoirs of A Geisha' was pretty good but not as good as I thought it was going to be.

Yesterday i got up, tidied up and then went to work. On my way i speant the last of my wages on a new top and a headband. After work I went and met Katey from work and we came to mine and got ready, Jess came round and we drove to the boat. Jerry my stepdad gave us free tickets for the boat, get in. We met Shaz, Holly and Emma. When we got to the Guildhall we met Ben, Dave, Rich, Geoof, and Holly.M. There were so many people there from the Island, it was insane.

Can't remember what the first band were called, but I dont really care. When Coheed & Cambria came on it was insane. After the intro they went into Welcome Home, it was so good, the pit was quite tight and we ended up drifting backwards. They played all of their 'hits' really and it was so fucking good, I actually love them, their amazing musicinas. When Thrice came on me and Katy stayed near the front for a while before drifting into the gnarliest pit ever, I went down and someone really hurt my back. We stood out for the rest of the set which was quite boring but Deadbolt and 'the artist in the ambulance' were good. Afterwards I ran Katey down to her boat then met the guys. ben gave me and Jess a lift home and I had a curry before going to sleep :)

Hope everyone else had a good weekend,

X

Hey evryone

  So it has been quite a while since i updated but these few first months of the year are going to be so busy and that. yesterday was quite a good day, after much sleep deprivation I got all of my art coursework handed in which was a big relief.

  In the afternoon I had my mock interview. Just before that some teacher confronted me about another teachers feelings about Battle Of the bands, I think i handled it really well especially considering this time last year I probably would have jsut started crying or not of had the confidence to put the event on in the first place. After discussing with everyone what happened I've decided they can stick their opinions where the sun doesnt shine because I have offered to let that person help and she pretty much told me where to go, how childish.

  I had my interview and I felt like it went really well, I didnt get any constructive criticism after it though which was a bit of a bummer but all the comments were really nice.

  Today has been fine, I didnt go to the gym with Eve as we first anticipated. I got back an essay which I did as prep for my exam on Wednesday and got the best marks in the class, woop! And I have got all arrangements for advertising at other highschools next week sorted.

Im supposed to be going out in Newport with my friend emma for her 18th birthday tonight but can't get hold of her :S Then tomorrow me and Eve are going to Chichester for Seb's rather belated birthday party, i hope its fun. I may pop into Gunwarf Quays in Portsmouth on Sunday and have a look in Monsoon at dressed for the Bays Ball.

I've lost 9 pounds on my diet :)

Have a good one, x

Have been such a busy bunny just recently what with Battle of the bands, Bedouin Soundclash, Psychology retake, Art Coursework, Pizza Hut, Seeing films about gay cowboys, Gym, Dieting, celebrating birthdays and the 6th month anniversary of the fire.

 

Yowza - hope to update properly soon, X

So I'm guessing it's time to update my LJ.

I went and stayed in Yorkshire with my family for New year, I had a really nice time, it was wonderful to meet them all and speand time away from home. I got a a bag and a locket from my auntie and cousin Sam for christmas which i was not expecting at all. Had such funny conversations with everyone of New Years Eve, was good to know the party was banging.

I got back on monday then Tuesday I met Katey and Amy in town and we went to Senior T's for lunch, was lush :) Wednesday i went back to school which was a bit gay seeing as I have so much coursework and stuff to do aswell as my retakes in the next couple of weeks.

Yesterday I had a very exciting meeting with my head teacher considering Battle of the bands. He is in company with the organisers of the Rock festival and basically they have offered us prizes. So now the event is not only going to be just a school competition but quite a pretigous and professionally run event, Im so excited about it, Amy, Chris, Luke and Danyn are all helping me out at the moment and were sorting things out so we can get the ball rolling. I have another meeting with the head on Monday, I can't wait.

School today was pointless, I got up and went in and my General Studies lesson has been cancelled and Eve was going to be late. Am going to go into town later and have a  look for some Jeans. I saw some in Next in brighton, and now taht i have to money to buy them I can't find them on the website, grr.

Holly is having her 18th burthday party tonight, hope to get pleasantly merry.

X

Can't believe I am updating today but I realy am quite bored.

Have had a good day but am feeling so incredibly rough. Got up at 6:30 and opened presents, I got lots of little bits and bobs, Perfume, a bag, a jumper, DVD's; Just general stuff really which i am all happy for recieving.

As usual I've eaten too much. I made a trfle earlier ate some after we got in from Chrismas Lunch at The Quay.

Am going to watch TV as soon as Dr.Who has finished,

Hope you've all had a good day,

X

Have done nothing but work for the past few days. It didnt feel like Christmas at all until this evening really.

Work was goo yesterday, speant most of my time gossiping and singing xmas carols with James. Then today Katie was back which was great, I have really missed her being there, also Benda put us on a till together so it was all good. I can't think of much else to write, katey came round quickly this evening for Hot Chocolate with Tia Lusso in it, yum yum. Errrrr, Im off to watch the goonies now, 1.5 hours to go, WOO!

 

Wishing You all a Great Christmas 2005,

 

X

Was so nice to have lie-in this onring, although Im now feeling really ill, damn it!

On Wednesday I got two fantastic pieces of post,

  • An offer from Bath Spa university for 220 points, (Yeah man!)
  • A letter requesting a meeting with the head master about my plans for 'Battle of the bands'

So I was in a pretty good mood and so decided to tidy my room. Katherine came around midday and we lounged about for most of the day and then got a takeway from Pizzahut and took it back to her place and watched School Of Rock. It was cool.

Yesterday I worked 9:30-6:30, it was fine though, I really enjoy working in the day, it's much nicer than my usual shift anyways. I'm doing 2:30-10:30 today which is a bit gay considering it's a friday and quite frankly I dont feel upto it, but I really do need the money so I'm going to go in anyways.

After work yesterday I went to Doris Pinks and met Eve, we went back to mine and had some Munch then went to the cinema to see King Kong. i did think it was good, I got slightly bored in parts and found some bits quite scary, and funny, but overall i think Peter Jackson did a good job of it.

This morning Eve left at 8:30 with my mum to go to work and I slept in till 9:30, got up and watched some music TV with Jack and Coral before getting a letter from Winchester in the post asking me to go to their open day in Feburary and saying that my offer is in the post, WOO!

So that has put me in a good frame of mind for today, Also I just remembered its:

2 MORE SLEEPS TILL CHRISTMAS!

:)X

Its been a good couple of days, I'm still fighting the bastard that is the Christmas bug.

Yesterday was our last day at school and so naturally, come lunch time we trashed the commonroom and had a party with mince pies and lots of chocolate, twas really nice. there were a few games of musical chair etc but we didnt join in, just sat on our table and talked. I'm so relieved to have my psychology coursework in for marking because it means that over the christmas period I can crack on with my Art stuff which is needed in when we go back to school in january.

I had a little bit of a lie-in this morning before getting ready for everyone to come round. Everyone came round between 11:45 and 12, and as I predicted Eve was first to come and Katey was last lol. We all walked down the Quay to Brewers Fayre where we got seated at two table of four because there wer 8 of us and no 8people tables :(. After some chat we exchanged our christmas gifts, I 'm so grateful for everything that I got:

Katey: Trevor Sorbie hair care
Eve: Darth tater (mr potatoe head) and A book about Green Day
Jess: Hair Clips and a Cross
Ele: Chocolates, personalised pencils and some Girl Boxers
Laura: Mittens and Bracelets

Woo :) I'm feeling slightly more Christmassy now which is all good. I had gammon for dinner followed by toffee waffle, I am now so unbelievably stuffed, and it didnt cost as much as I assumed, so its smiles all round, :)

I have a day free from work tomorrow in which I intend to crack on with some art, and then Its work for me, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday.

X

 

Ps - I got a postcard from Winchester, theyve got my application.

Well now..

Woke up rather late yesterday and feeling wuite worse for wear. Had to start work at 1 so I dragged myself up and out of bed. Work was fine though I had the worst headache I've had in a long while. I saw Eve and Sophie which was cool. And Seb's Dad and younger sister were in the store bag-packing for charity which I thought was really nice.

I came home last night and watched 'Good Will Hunting', it's such a good film, my Nan gave it to me. It also has the one and only : Matt Damon in it, so yeah.

Went to work today which was quite pointless seeing as I didnt feel up to it at all. Worked for 2hours before my boss said I could go home. I have some psychology to finish this evening... ho hum.

Still awaiting a reply from Red Funnel and for uni offers, its only been 2 and a half weeks since my application went off, puh!

 

Hope you've all had a good weekend, X

I have just e-mailed a letter of complaint to Red Funnel telling them how Gay i think they are due to their infrquent ferries at midnight. I could so be the next Mary Whitehouse, but I think shes far too lonely.

Anyhow. I had a good day at school although none of my 'girlfriends' (that sounds so cheerleader like) were in this monring so I hung out with the lads most of this morning and played silly games on Tom's laptop. My lesson was quite funny thismorning, I do like General Studies. 

It started raining as I left school and so Lin gave me a lift into town. I saw loads of people which was embarrasing seeing as I looked so rough. Came home and chilled before having a fight with my sister and then going to Katey's for a Thai Green Curry. It was really nice, cheers mate.

I got home and watched Johnathan Ross and am now waiting for my step-dad to arrive home, he's buying my Isle Of Wight Festival 'early bird' tickets as we speak.

I start work at 1 tomorrow and then am going to Holly's party for a while with Seb, Eva and Jesskins.

Really could do with a cold pint of XXXX right now, weird.

 

 

To whom it may concern,

I am writing to you concerning problems that my peers and I have encountered recently when using your services. We appreciate that it is winter and so your ferries are not running as frequently as they may do at other times during the year, however the fact that there is neither a hi-speed or a car ferry that operates at midnight has lead us to encounter many problems when travelling to and from the Island. I am sure that I am not the only person that feels that this is an inconvenience and would just like to notify you of this problem.

Many thanks.

Didnt have such a good start to the week, was being such a twat. Monday was a really shite day.

On Tuesday I went to So'ton with Katey, Ele and Jess to see Trashlight. One of the support bands : Plastic Toys, were absolutely amazing but the others were crap and we never got to see Trashlight due to our travel arrangements, it totally sucked, I hate this Island sometimes, but I did get to spend some good time with Jess which was cool.

Went into school yesterday and was really hyper. We had christmas lunch from the canteen which made me feel sick. Then Kev turned up whcih was cool as I havent seen him for ages, :) Picked my brother up and came home to carry on with my Psychology coursework.

I speant all of time this monring doing Psychology with Christine, Rich and Poods, we got it all done, all I have to do now is my discussion and abstract which is a relief because when he hands it back to me all I'll have to do is the corections. Hung out at lunch before English which was actually quite enjoyable. After school we said goodbye to Eve before I waled into town with Laura, Amy and Ele. I left them at the Quay where I met Katie and Amber. Was really nice see them as I havent seen either of them for ages! Katie is looking so much better than she did last time I saw her.

Am now looking forward to Little Britain tonight.

Yetserday I met my friend Katherine in town after doing some much needed Christmas Shopping. We had a Mr.T's for lunch and then went to see The Lion The Witch and the wardrobe. I think it was fantastic, probably my favourite adaptation of it so far. In the evening we had to take my brother and my next door neighbour's children to their school disco, you can probably imagine the fun.

This morning I lounged around a bit and shopped online before going to work. Work was pretty cool actually, the shift went fast, I saw Hannah, Robin and Sam whcih cheered me up, I went to French Franks and saw Katey for lunch and got my Christmas hours, which ROCK! :) I'm really happy, my boss has been nice to me for once. Bought some wrapping paper and stuff and came home.

I'm now waiting for Eve and my Mother to come home from the 'Doris Pinks' Christmas Party. Me and Eve are going shopping in Southampton tommorrow, :)

Good weekends everyone x

And before I forget -

Stolen From::
You reply to this post, and I'll tell you one (or maybe even several) of the reasons I like/love/adore you. Then, of course, you put this in your own journal, and spread the love. Can't say fairer than that!

My ever huge mountain of school work is growing once more.

On Sunday I worked until 5, afterwards me and Christine met rich and walked back to Christine's to get on with our Psychology homework. We didnt actually get an awful lot done, we endded up watching the Never Ending Story and drinking Hot Chocolate with Baileys in it.

Yesterday I found out in Art that the hand-in date for our coursework is on Monday, so I know what I'll be doing this weekend. After a quite eventful lesson I left school with Katey and went to the Riverside Centre to give a blood donation for the first time.

I had to fill out quite a few papers about my medical and sexual history and also had to have my blood tested for Iron levels. It didnt hurt, I actually quite enjoyed it. My blood flow was really dlow and so they couldnt take enough from me for a whole donation which is a bit gay and probably due to the fact that i don't drink enough liquids.
